 On the Luclin server I thought I had found what it was I was missing. Purpose. So, I set out to recreate a guild I had started in UO there. Well, one good reason I left UO was because I had burnt out as a GM, all work and no play they say... So another move  this one to Torv. That was around the time Kunark went live.I was always expecting to find the magic answer to my purpose goal, always thought hey lets see if I can find it here.. I always found greedy, self centered, non-roleplaying folk who would rather farm Crushbone belts than help someone out in even the smallest way.<br>
 On Thouluxe I came close, 8 levels close. But with the ultimate prrize that close the best guild I have ever been apart of crumbled around us, founding members gone off to greener pastures which soone enough withered there as well.I knew or thought I knew most of the reasoning behind the fall, and when I heard that the RP server was finally being made I knew this would be my home. <br>
 I have roleplayed more here in 7 days played then all of the 50 plus hours on all other characters I have ever played. There are fine folks I have never intereacted with here because as an elf I simply do not understand them. I am sure there are some royal pains here, but there are not too many of anykind and those who are will have to suffer their own company as they advance, I will not put up with them here.<br>
 There are alot of really good folk here and this is where I can finally put down some roots.The rule set mandates planning, it rewards guilds and team work. It sets realistic linguistic obsticals in your way. It supports a world where most folks would choose to associate with their own kind. The economy is how it should be, and the challenges are greater because you have to EARN almost everything.<br>
 I can hardly stomach logging into an &quot;old&quot; server any  longer. The banded mail I where is home crafted(1st time smith), I love it here and plan on staying. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BakoFV</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Ladies Leezard</span><br>  Posts: 141<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/7/02 6:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Moving to Firiona Vie? Read here first</span><hr size=1> I have played on 5 servers, Prexus, Morrel Thule, Test, Luclin and Now Firiona Vie, and By Far Firiona Vie is the best.<br>
<br>
Coming to Firiona Vie will be a very challanging task for anyone who wishes to join, You have alot of Obsticles to overcome such as Language Barrier, Trivial Loot Code, Low population. But once you get over these small problems, The Joy in wich you will feel is like no other in the game.<br>
<br>
I am not much of a Roleplayer because I am not very good at it, and in Turn I have created the only Guild who doesnt actively roleplay. We do However Try to roleplay to others outside of guild, and many members do Roleplay frequesntly. Its a joy just to walk around and talk with people because everyone is so nice and polite, This server has the greatest dencity of GOOD people as I have ever seen.<br>
<br>
So If you thinking of Joining Firiona Vie, and You like a challenge, I think this would be the place you want to be. The Reward of this server as your character as a person, Will be 10 fold the difficult journey you have to travel. <p>Bako Emberfist<BR>
