<br>
It is very important to keep in mind the TLC when you start a character on FV.  Quests should really be done in the levels that they are meant to be done, this, and many of the other rules will hamper your leveling speed.. But thats part of why you are here isn't it?<br>
<br>
Languages too, require a substantial amount of time and thought.  I reccomend finding a friend or group of friends to play with early on.  Religiously work on languages, every hour, or every zone, get taught a point of something, anything.  I expect it will be well into the 50's before I am fluent in everything I want to be.<br>
<br>
The server is filled with friendly, helpful, roleplaying types.  The few times I have run into a dewd, I just switch to another language and type a bunch of question marks and /boggle /nod /smile and /em shakes his head in bemusement.  End of problem.  <br>
<br>
The lack of a real player market does hurt.  Prices seem to be lower in general though, if you can find what you want.  Maybe because the plat is distributed more evenly.  If you really want something you will have to post on the market here, and hope that the 2% of players that also read message boards has what you want, otherwise plan on camping it yourself or with friends. <br>
<br>
I am guild shy, being twice or is it thrice bitten, but I have mostly heard good abhout the guilds I have read about, even the &quot;ubers&quot;, we will see how that develops though, as the big crowd hits the 50's, maybe 6 months from now <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...<br>
