<br>
Second thing, of course, is the new ruleset.  In some ways it's an impediment to both normal play and role-play.  In other ways, it likely contributes to keeping this server small.  Small is very good.  It means no one can be anonymous for long and thus griefers won't like it here.  'Course it also makes it hard to form pickup-groups.  I'd say that if you don't plan on joining a guild sometime before your class hits it's personal &quot;solo-wall&quot;, FV probably isn't for you.<br>
<br>
In general, FV brings back memories of how EQ was just weeks after release.  Everyone at least makes a stab at role-playing and people here mostly want to have fun grouping together rather than rushing like mad lemmings from one hot-loot spot to the next.  Read the rule-set on Verant's web site and if the deviations from normal servers sounds tolerable to you, come try FV.  It's a lot of fun. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/13/02 8:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm48.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Do you have questions about how to learn a language here?</span><hr size=1> Well then, you're not alone!  I've just put together a quick FAQ on this topic at this thread:<br>
