<br>
On the flip side, Firiona Vie has plenty to offer those who willing to put up with a little difficulty.  Most ogres and trolls that practice d00d-speak don't bother other races simply because they don't speak the same language.  Roleplaying is something that other players look up to, rather than look down on, and will spontaneously join in on just for the fun of it.  And the market on Firiona Vie is, in my opinion, more friendly for those who wish to tradeskill for profit at the lower end.  Not always a great profit, but still better than what i've seen on Cazic-Thule.<br>
<br>
