<br>
as many above, i came to Firiona Vie for the roleplay. And to be honest, i am both surprised and disappointed. Surprised at the amount and quality of roleplay i find, and disappointed since there seem to be many who just dont care... or dont do it.<br>
Dont get me wrong - everyone can play there, but i wonder why people who dont even attempt to roleplay.<br>
Luckily, those are few.<br>
<br>
I agree with most posts before. Newbies will find Firiona Vie a lot more difficult than other blue servers. On the other hand, it is also more interesting. There are very few zones which give a similar feel as they do on other servers. It is a rare thing not to find something suitable to hunt, at least once you realized what you *can* hunt safely.<br>
<br>
Language barriers, alignment barriers, trade restriction and the lack of &quot;alts&quot; on the same server all place a higher value on things you obtain or do yourself. It is an experience, and one i personally enjoy a lot.<br>
<br>
Friends are also a lot more valuable in my eyes. The chance of running into a zone and finding a group just by shouting or adding the LFG tag is low (At least for my dark elf it rarely works). Finding friends can be a pain - but  the ones you do find tend to stick around a lot more than on 'normal' blue server. They most likely are just as glad having you as friend, as you are to have them.<br>
<br>
There is a lot less twinking, and yes, a lot less farming too, because the player market is a lot more difficult to handle. I rather like that. It makes special items special. Not every second necromancer runs around with a harvester (Just an example - i dont know if they do truly). I personally did not manage to sell a single piece of equipment, and rarely am able to purchase anything.<br>
<br>
So, my bottom line is - If you look for a challenge, roleplay, and having a good time with others who do the same, Firiona Vie might be for you. If you look for an uber guild, fast leveling, the best possible equipment, you'd probably be better off somewhere else. <br>
