er to get attached to it.  It will help you get a feel for the environment of the game, the spells, the system of travel, the expectations, in an environment where you're extremely likely to be twinked from birth.  In other words, you can learn the ropes, basic grouping skills, and anything else, such as corpse running, in a place where you can most likely get help easily through /ooc.  Of course, if you're confident, have read the manual cover to cover, then by all means, dive straight in.  There's a nice community of people here that are more than willing to help you.<br>
